{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"914043ed-d538-43b0-a502-2130bb5e5763","content":"**Best tool: `dotnet-trace`** — it's lightweight, easy to use, and built for .NET.\n\n### Quick steps:\n\n```powershell\n# 1. Install the tool (one-time)\ndotnet tool install --global dotnet-trace\n\n# 2. Find your process ID\ndotnet-trace ps\n\n# 3. Collect a 30-second CPU profile\ndotnet-trace collect -p <PID> --profile cpu-sampling --duration 00:00:30\n```\n\nThis produces a `.nettrace` file you can open in **Visual Studio** (Diagnostics Hub) or **PerfView**.\n\n### Alternative: PerfView (deeper analysis)\nIf you need kernel-level detail (e.g., thread contention, I/O stalls mixed with CPU):\n\n```powershell\n# Download from https://github.com/microsoft/perfview/releases\nPerfView.exe collect -Duration:30 -CircularMB:500\n```\n\n### When to use which:\n\n| Tool | Best for |\n|---|---|\n| `dotnet-trace` | Quick managed-code CPU sampling, low overhead |\n| **PerfView** | Deep dives — ETW events, GC analysis, kernel + managed stacks |\n\n**Tip:** If the service is unresponsive, prefer `dotnet-trace` — it attaches via EventPipe with minimal additional load. Collect for 20–30 seconds, then analyze the flame graph in VS to find your hot path.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b0b64b5b-4fc2-4e1b-a25e-408eba0102f9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking for guidance on collecting a CPU trace for a .NET 8 service on Windows Server. This is a knowledge/advice question, not a code task. I should provide a concise, practical answer.\n\nThe best tool for this is `dotnet-trace` or PerfView. For CPU profiling specifically, `dotnet-trace` with the cpu-sampling profile is the simplest, but PerfView gives richer ETW-based analysis. Since they have admin access and it's Windows, PerfView is the gold standard for CPU investigation on Windows .NET apps.\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":499,"requestId":"215A:1F2F04:6103B44:69B8EE0:69F00CD2"},"id":"6d91f3b5-e557-405f-bc2b-7f90f813bf74","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:26:55.383Z","parentId":"34fbb512-a4b7-4919-ad18-9634972f45af"}
